1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:05,360
This series is a work of fiction inspired by
questions that arise within the human heart.

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:09,760
It is not intended to offend or pass judgment
on any beliefs, religions, or individuals.

3
00:00:12,004 --> 00:00:13,440
(Previous Chapter)
Sorry.

4
00:00:13,734 --> 00:00:16,404
Wow! That's our Christmas play couple
right there.

5
00:00:16,551 --> 00:00:18,797
Joseph and the Virgin Mary.

6
00:00:20,518 --> 00:00:22,400
Cherry asked me
to be in the Christmas play.

7
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:24,250
What does it have to do with me?

8
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:26,201
I want you to be okay with it.

9
00:00:30,610 --> 00:00:31,998
Tanrak, why are you running?

10
00:00:32,380 --> 00:00:33,380
I'm not running.

11
00:00:33,601 --> 00:00:35,097
You're running from yourself.

12
00:00:37,244 --> 00:00:38,899
I'm not God's favorite son.

13
00:00:39,931 --> 00:00:42,102
Tanrak, I like you.

14
00:00:44,736 --> 00:00:46,773
I'm not God's favorite son either.

15
00:00:49,980 --> 00:00:51,102
What about you, Tanrak?

16
00:00:52,025 --> 00:00:53,197
Have you ever had doubts?

17
00:00:53,838 --> 00:00:54,903
Actually,

18
00:00:57,351 --> 00:00:58,703
I do have doubts sometimes.

19
00:01:00,854 --> 00:01:04,201
My heart isn't that steady.

20
00:01:04,837 --> 00:01:05,976
There are still…

21
00:01:07,470 --> 00:01:08,702
things that…

22
00:01:09,355 --> 00:01:10,502
make me…

23
00:01:10,776 --> 00:01:11,896
waver.

24
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:22,520
LOVE IS PATIENT
1 CORINTHIANS 13:4–7

25
00:01:24,531 --> 00:01:27,800
Jesus said to His disciples,

26
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,902
“This is My commandment:

27
00:01:30,287 --> 00:01:34,302
Love one another as I have loved you.

28
00:01:35,183 --> 00:01:38,380
No one has greater love than this:

29
00:01:38,997 --> 00:01:41,899
to lay down one's life for one's friends.”

30
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,490
Dear brothers and sisters,

31
00:01:49,804 --> 00:01:51,801
I'd like to thank you all

32
00:01:52,122 --> 00:01:54,797
for your donations to Magdalene Church

33
00:01:54,835 --> 00:01:57,195
and for helping us
through Christmas so smoothly.

34
00:01:58,299 --> 00:01:59,299
Uh, everyone.

35
00:01:59,414 --> 00:02:02,380
Keep anything we can still use.

36
00:02:02,459 --> 00:02:04,899
Throw out the broken ones.

37
00:02:05,103 --> 00:02:06,103
Yes.

38
00:02:10,022 --> 00:02:12,130
Come on, keep it up.

39
00:02:12,437 --> 00:02:14,201
We can use them again next year.

40
00:02:15,367 --> 00:02:16,367
Tanrak.

41
00:02:16,506 --> 00:02:17,527
Could you get some people

42
00:02:17,564 --> 00:02:19,804
to pack up the lucky-dip booth
outside for me?

43
00:02:20,242 --> 00:02:21,580
It's already done, Father.

44
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:23,690
I assigned the younger boys to handle it.

45
00:02:23,835 --> 00:02:24,905
Excellent.

46
00:02:28,235 --> 00:02:30,397
Let's save this for later.

47
00:03:05,259 --> 00:03:06,330
You can just take it.

48
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,303
I'll print a new one.

49
00:03:18,390 --> 00:03:19,503
Can I keep this?

50
00:03:19,918 --> 00:03:20,918
Sure.

51
00:03:21,216 --> 00:03:22,216
I'll print another one.

52
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,620
Wait.

53
00:03:28,730 --> 00:03:30,401
You don't want my picture at all?

54
00:03:31,315 --> 00:03:32,998
I do. I'll take all of them.

55
00:03:34,245 --> 00:03:35,985
Huh. I thought, like,

56
00:03:36,623 --> 00:03:39,204
the rector banned photos
with girls or something.

57
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:40,960
No idea.

58
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:42,854
But I've seen people have them.

59
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:44,740
They do.

60
00:03:45,056 --> 00:03:46,202
Tons of them, actually.

61
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:49,004
Just don't get caught.

62
00:03:50,038 --> 00:03:50,700
Right?

63
00:03:50,816 --> 00:03:51,902
This is Phai.

64
00:03:52,620 --> 00:03:54,499
And this is Barth. Tanrak's friend.

65
00:04:00,223 --> 00:04:02,100
Yeah. He's my boyfriend.

66
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:05,804
So…

67
00:04:06,170 --> 00:04:08,597
can church scholarship boys
seriously date someone?

68
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,520
I don't think so.

69
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:16,767
Maybe not.

70
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:18,170
I don't know.

71
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:20,350
Really?

72
00:04:20,810 --> 00:04:21,810
Is that so?

73
00:04:24,191 --> 00:04:25,191
Me?

74
00:04:26,487 --> 00:04:27,499
I don't have anyone.

75
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,600
That's sad.

76
00:04:32,179 --> 00:04:34,930
Having to keep it to yourself
if you like someone.

77
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:39,954
But as a church scholarship boy,

78
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:42,910
you probably shouldn't even like anyone
to begin with, right?

79
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,400
You liked me.

80
00:04:46,997 --> 00:04:47,997
What?

81
00:04:48,385 --> 00:04:49,702
Didn't you like me first?

82
00:04:53,725 --> 00:04:54,896
Can we go eat now?

83
00:04:55,911 --> 00:04:57,102
- Let's go.
- See you.

84
00:04:58,068 --> 00:04:59,068
See you.

85
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:08,130
Babe, you're heavy.

86
00:05:08,371 --> 00:05:10,300
How could you say that?

87
00:05:10,417 --> 00:05:11,417
Ow!

88
00:05:11,832 --> 00:05:12,600
Let's go.

89
00:05:12,642 --> 00:05:13,642
Okay.

90
00:05:57,030 --> 00:05:58,030
What are you doing?

91
00:06:02,343 --> 00:06:03,343
It's a secret.

92
00:06:04,742 --> 00:06:05,742
A secret?

93
00:06:07,422 --> 00:06:08,897
So we're keeping secrets now?

94
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:20,670
Oh!

95
00:06:24,653 --> 00:06:26,850
Hey, Tan! You'll tear it.

96
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,197
It's the only one I have.

97
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,000
Where did you get it?

98
00:06:36,811 --> 00:06:38,100
I asked Cherry for it.

99
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:42,998
It's a cute picture.

100
00:06:44,848 --> 00:06:45,848
Can I have it?

101
00:06:46,854 --> 00:06:47,854
No.

102
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,490
This is rare, you know.

103
00:06:55,173 --> 00:06:56,173
Barth.

104
00:07:00,908 --> 00:07:01,908
What?

105
00:07:02,795 --> 00:07:03,795
Let's trade.

106
00:07:06,545 --> 00:07:08,697
I saw you take that from the trash pile.

107
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,480
Well…

108
00:07:12,419 --> 00:07:14,997
It felt like a waste to throw it away.

109
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:16,802
And I thought…

110
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:18,170
it…

111
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:20,903
kind of looks like you.

112
00:07:24,005 --> 00:07:25,005
Let me see.

113
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:27,200
Here. See?

114
00:07:29,170 --> 00:07:30,170
Doesn't it now?

115
00:07:36,550 --> 00:07:37,550
No, it doesn't.

116
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,577
What kind of trade is that?

117
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:40,780
Come on.

118
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:49,797
Fine. I'm losing out here, you know?

119
00:07:50,118 --> 00:07:52,450
Losing out how?
You got the photo for free.

120
00:07:52,511 --> 00:07:53,980
You got that for free too.

121
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,198
Let me see the photo.

122
00:08:03,136 --> 00:08:04,595
Your face looks so funny.

123
00:08:05,302 --> 00:08:06,170
Hey, Barth.

124
00:08:06,207 --> 00:08:07,751
Father needs help moving tables.

125
00:08:07,777 --> 00:08:08,777
Hurry.

126
00:08:09,031 --> 00:08:10,198
Yeah, I'll be there.

127
00:08:17,419 --> 00:08:18,702
I should go help them.

128
00:08:19,188 --> 00:08:20,788
Or they will say I'm slacking off again.

129
00:08:25,949 --> 00:08:27,103
Take good care of it.

130
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:11,000
"Ticket to Heaven"
(Episode 4)

131
00:10:17,244 --> 00:10:19,185
What's this?

132
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:21,099
You're tired already?

133
00:10:21,570 --> 00:10:23,890
Father, Ryu kept complaining
the whole time.

134
00:10:23,906 --> 00:10:24,906
It's true.

135
00:10:25,047 --> 00:10:26,099
No, Father.

136
00:10:26,237 --> 00:10:27,362
I worked the hardest.

137
00:10:27,577 --> 00:10:29,300
I could carry chairs for ten more rounds.

138
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:33,251
I saw you slacking off right after Mass.

139
00:10:33,278 --> 00:10:34,780
What? That's not true, Prince.

140
00:10:34,945 --> 00:10:36,340
You didn't help with anything.

141
00:10:36,373 --> 00:10:37,490
It's all right.

142
00:10:37,685 --> 00:10:39,958
God will remember
who didn't abandon their work

143
00:10:39,985 --> 00:10:41,802
even when they were tired.

144
00:10:43,829 --> 00:10:46,500
Since I can see
you're all genuinely tired today,

145
00:10:46,918 --> 00:10:49,509
I'll give you extra movie time tonight.

146
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:50,550
Yay!

147
00:10:50,585 --> 00:10:51,990
If anyone wants to watch anything,

148
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:54,398
go tell Master Phak
so he can rent it for you.

149
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,410
Sit with me during the movie.

150
00:11:00,505 --> 00:11:02,933
All right,
go take care of your own things.

151
00:11:02,962 --> 00:11:03,962
Go on.

152
00:11:35,124 --> 00:11:36,124
Ryu, move.

153
00:11:36,322 --> 00:11:37,322
What?

154
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:39,370
Move. Come on.

155
00:11:39,691 --> 00:11:40,902
What the hell?

156
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:09,850
Oh, Tanrak.

157
00:12:10,002 --> 00:12:11,980
Your group has to help
with traffic duty tomorrow.

158
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,859
I need you to go a bit earlier.

159
00:12:14,137 --> 00:12:15,137
Okay.

160
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,000
Keep an eye on your friends too.

161
00:12:32,819 --> 00:12:34,000
Want to trade blankets?

162
00:12:37,585 --> 00:12:38,585
Sure.

163
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:51,271
♪ Every second that I have you near ♪

164
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:55,700
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

165
00:12:56,127 --> 00:13:01,263
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

166
00:13:01,496 --> 00:13:04,650
♪ And hold this moment
for as long as I can ♪

167
00:13:04,810 --> 00:13:09,133
♪ If heaven is real,
how beautiful could it be ♪

168
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:13,600
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

169
00:13:14,081 --> 00:13:18,795
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

170
00:13:18,906 --> 00:13:25,330
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

171
00:13:40,930 --> 00:13:43,611
♪ Every second ♪
♪ From that moment ♪

172
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,099
♪ I have you near ♪
♪ I have you near ♪

173
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:49,762
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

174
00:13:49,989 --> 00:13:55,102
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

175
00:13:55,328 --> 00:13:58,601
♪ And hold this moment
for as long as I can ♪

176
00:13:58,630 --> 00:14:01,183
♪ If heaven is real ♪
♪ If it's not real ♪

177
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:03,414
♪ How beautiful could it be ♪

178
00:14:03,432 --> 00:14:07,445
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

179
00:14:07,897 --> 00:14:12,622
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

180
00:14:12,672 --> 00:14:19,610
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

181
00:14:22,722 --> 00:14:23,722
Tanrak.

182
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,597
Tanrak, rotten head boy!

183
00:14:26,842 --> 00:14:28,201
Hand out the report books.

184
00:14:28,552 --> 00:14:30,296
- Yes?
- Come get the report books.

185
00:14:30,348 --> 00:14:31,348
Oh.

186
00:14:34,195 --> 00:14:37,487
For the scholarship students,
Father has added his comments already.

187
00:14:37,518 --> 00:14:40,002
Make sure you read them
and sign to acknowledge them.

188
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:43,570
So, how did everyone do this term?

189
00:14:43,837 --> 00:14:45,056
Full marks? Full marks?

190
00:14:45,706 --> 00:14:46,706
Full zero.

191
00:14:47,922 --> 00:14:49,897
Hey! Joe's here!

192
00:14:50,374 --> 00:14:51,582
Wow!

193
00:14:52,946 --> 00:14:55,576
Joe's here?

194
00:14:56,085 --> 00:14:57,800
Hey, what's with you all?

195
00:14:58,339 --> 00:15:00,296
You're acting like
your seniors are celebrities.

196
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:02,000
I'm better-looking than him.

197
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:03,071
Boo!

198
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:06,600
Okay, then.

199
00:15:07,102 --> 00:15:10,780
For guidance period,
go find an activity you want to join.

200
00:15:11,057 --> 00:15:12,502
Okay. That's all for today.

201
00:15:12,727 --> 00:15:14,379
Class.

202
00:15:14,804 --> 00:15:17,195
Thank you.

203
00:15:23,671 --> 00:15:26,202
Promotion readiness, 4.5.

204
00:15:27,106 --> 00:15:28,106
Tan.

205
00:15:28,185 --> 00:15:29,797
What did Father write for you?

206
00:15:29,992 --> 00:15:30,764
What?

207
00:15:30,795 --> 00:15:32,100
What score did you get?

208
00:15:32,189 --> 00:15:34,450
Give me a sec. I have to go.

209
00:15:35,066 --> 00:15:36,297
See you. Thanks.

210
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:46,170
SENIORS GUIDING JUNIORS

211
00:15:46,271 --> 00:15:47,597
You can sign up first.

212
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,902
Hey, who's this? I don't know him.

213
00:15:56,423 --> 00:15:57,442
Barth. He's new.

214
00:15:57,665 --> 00:15:59,601
- Hello.
- Oh. Hi. Have a seat.

215
00:16:00,053 --> 00:16:01,613
Barth, do you want to go to university?

216
00:16:02,348 --> 00:16:03,348
Come on.

217
00:16:07,182 --> 00:16:08,001
Hi, Joe.

218
00:16:08,155 --> 00:16:09,155
Oh, hi.

219
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:11,050
Is that you, Tanrak?

220
00:16:11,687 --> 00:16:13,000
You've gotten so much taller.

221
00:16:14,814 --> 00:16:15,568
Yeah.

222
00:16:15,765 --> 00:16:17,503
You haven't changed at all.

223
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,102
I have.

224
00:16:20,816 --> 00:16:23,097
Seminary is a whole different world
from here.

225
00:16:25,540 --> 00:16:26,540
Really?

226
00:16:27,060 --> 00:16:28,601
Is it… tough?

227
00:16:29,595 --> 00:16:30,595
Not tough.

228
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:32,903
It's just really quiet.

229
00:16:33,891 --> 00:16:36,597
So quiet I sometimes wonder
what I'm doing there.

230
00:16:38,736 --> 00:16:41,402
Well, if you want to see lots of girls,
or get a girlfriend,

231
00:16:41,765 --> 00:16:43,500
this is the way to go, right?

232
00:16:43,647 --> 00:16:44,647
Am I right?

233
00:16:45,579 --> 00:16:48,997
Weren't you at seminary at first, Bank?

234
00:16:49,825 --> 00:16:51,699
Another one changing their mind.

235
00:16:52,986 --> 00:16:54,397
Like I said, it's hard.

236
00:16:55,099 --> 00:16:56,496
Everyone wants to have someone.

237
00:16:58,146 --> 00:17:00,401
But we have our own kind of love.

238
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,640
You get it, right?

239
00:17:03,762 --> 00:17:04,780
What kind of love?

240
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,902
The kind that doesn't belong
to just one person.

241
00:17:11,728 --> 00:17:13,004
Of course it gets boring.

242
00:17:13,060 --> 00:17:14,900
Having to make up with your girlfriend?

243
00:17:15,291 --> 00:17:16,026
Such a pain.

244
00:17:16,060 --> 00:17:17,485
Even a bad boy worries.

245
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:19,137
“What should I do?” Right?

246
00:17:19,192 --> 00:17:20,503
It's so much drama.

247
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,100
You'll understand once it happens to you.

248
00:17:23,278 --> 00:17:25,001
When you get to university, I'll tell you.

249
00:17:25,386 --> 00:17:26,130
I'll show you around.

250
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,496
I know you all have a lot
on your minds right now.

251
00:17:29,790 --> 00:17:30,808
It's not strange.

252
00:17:31,604 --> 00:17:32,903
I was the same at your age.

253
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:35,770
But if your heart is pulling you
somewhere else,

254
00:17:35,790 --> 00:17:36,808
don't force it.

255
00:17:37,875 --> 00:17:39,235
But don't run away from it either.

256
00:17:40,302 --> 00:17:41,897
Listen carefully to your heart.

257
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:58,299
When your parents come
pick you up tomorrow,

258
00:17:58,490 --> 00:18:00,497
don't forget to take the gifts home.

259
00:18:01,309 --> 00:18:05,600
If your family already has a calendar,
you don't have to take one.

260
00:18:07,422 --> 00:18:08,422
Yes, Father.

261
00:18:09,127 --> 00:18:10,401
Get it done tonight.

262
00:18:13,189 --> 00:18:14,189
Barth.

263
00:18:14,699 --> 00:18:15,897
This one smells nice.

264
00:18:16,863 --> 00:18:19,302
But it smells familiar.

265
00:18:20,656 --> 00:18:21,897
I can't put my finger on it.

266
00:18:22,506 --> 00:18:23,506
Smell it.

267
00:18:27,579 --> 00:18:28,897
- Right?
- It smells…

268
00:18:30,539 --> 00:18:31,900
like Father's room, doesn't it?

269
00:18:34,330 --> 00:18:35,900
Yeah. That's it.

270
00:18:38,127 --> 00:18:42,127
Da-da-da-da-da-da!

271
00:18:42,870 --> 00:18:44,499
Hurry up. We're going home tomorrow.

272
00:18:46,031 --> 00:18:47,302
Look at you, Ryu.

273
00:18:47,795 --> 00:18:49,696
You're so pumped to go home.

274
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:52,850
My mom said she'd take me to Dan Neramit.
I'll enjoy it for you guys.

275
00:18:53,056 --> 00:18:55,176
But you were singing
the Siam Amazing Park theme song?

276
00:18:56,189 --> 00:18:57,302
Just going home.

277
00:18:57,518 --> 00:18:58,850
Why is he so happy?

278
00:19:02,670 --> 00:19:04,595
I mean,

279
00:19:05,548 --> 00:19:06,903
break is kind of nice.

280
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:10,610
When school is empty, it feels like
the whole place belongs to you.

281
00:19:14,888 --> 00:19:16,410
But this year, you're staying with me.

282
00:19:34,598 --> 00:19:35,598
Tan.

283
00:19:35,921 --> 00:19:37,598
Have you signed up with Joe yet?

284
00:19:39,783 --> 00:19:42,699
Joe said I don't have to decide yet.

285
00:19:46,734 --> 00:19:47,800
Right. And…

286
00:19:48,426 --> 00:19:49,997
what did Father write for you?

287
00:19:52,851 --> 00:19:53,851
Oh.

288
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:56,002
I left my report book at school.

289
00:20:05,762 --> 00:20:08,001
I thought you'd take this more seriously.

290
00:20:33,878 --> 00:20:36,400
Safe travels, everyone. God bless.

291
00:20:40,038 --> 00:20:42,459
Father, I'll get going now.

292
00:20:42,488 --> 00:20:43,247
Hello.

293
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:44,601
- Hello, Father.
- Hello, Father.

294
00:20:44,632 --> 00:20:46,167
We brought some fruit from our orchard.

295
00:20:46,191 --> 00:20:49,179
Dragon fruit and oranges.

296
00:20:49,499 --> 00:20:50,339
Thank you.

297
00:20:50,377 --> 00:20:53,297
They may not look perfect,
but they're really good.

298
00:20:53,573 --> 00:20:55,334
You didn't have to bring anything.

299
00:20:55,362 --> 00:20:56,497
I feel bad.

300
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:58,300
You've already come such a long way.

301
00:20:58,850 --> 00:21:00,099
It's just a small gift.

302
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:03,002
It's nothing compared to how much
you've helped our family

303
00:21:04,026 --> 00:21:07,696
by giving Kongdech a scholarship here
for a bright future.

304
00:21:08,580 --> 00:21:10,502
I'm not the only one
who gave him this chance.

305
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:14,201
Kongdech works very hard.

306
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,503
He always helps out
at the scholarship dorm.

307
00:21:17,173 --> 00:21:18,198
That's good, son.

308
00:21:18,417 --> 00:21:21,001
Make sure you give back
to the church and the priests.

309
00:21:21,257 --> 00:21:23,195
See? You always say I don't do anything.

310
00:21:25,936 --> 00:21:27,576
Here is a scented candle.

311
00:21:28,354 --> 00:21:29,971
- Thank you, Father.
- Thank you.

312
00:21:30,903 --> 00:21:32,804
And this is a calendar.

313
00:21:33,373 --> 00:21:35,499
It has all the important dates.

314
00:21:35,709 --> 00:21:38,097
People in the village can use it too.

315
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:40,002
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

316
00:21:41,296 --> 00:21:42,899
Oh, Tanrak.

317
00:21:43,065 --> 00:21:44,065
What a shame.

318
00:21:44,093 --> 00:21:46,598
I thought you'd come home with us.

319
00:21:46,653 --> 00:21:47,693
Oh.

320
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:51,210
Oh, right. I brought you a gift too.

321
00:21:51,402 --> 00:21:52,402
Thank you.

322
00:21:54,487 --> 00:21:55,640
Have a safe trip.

323
00:21:55,669 --> 00:21:57,265
We'll get going now, Father.

324
00:21:57,296 --> 00:21:58,782
- Goodbye, Father.
- Goodbye, Father.

325
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:01,797
Let's go, son.

326
00:22:02,112 --> 00:22:03,296
Hey. See you later.

327
00:22:27,841 --> 00:22:28,841
Hey.

328
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:30,902
That shirt is so cool.

329
00:22:31,669 --> 00:22:32,697
Did you just get it?

330
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:35,696
Kongdech's mom bought it for me.

331
00:22:40,285 --> 00:22:41,983
Who gets a gift and looks this grumpy?

332
00:22:44,454 --> 00:22:45,798
His mom is nice.

333
00:22:46,631 --> 00:22:47,800
But him?

334
00:22:48,616 --> 00:22:49,970
He sulks over everything.

335
00:22:53,250 --> 00:22:54,299
About the other day?

336
00:22:56,994 --> 00:22:57,865
I mean,

337
00:22:57,899 --> 00:22:59,896
I just forgot my report book.

338
00:23:00,669 --> 00:23:02,500
He didn't have to get this upset.

339
00:23:06,290 --> 00:23:07,903
You're closest to Kongdech, right?

340
00:23:09,854 --> 00:23:10,854
Well,

341
00:23:11,128 --> 00:23:12,600
probably the closest.

342
00:23:16,191 --> 00:23:17,402
Just watch.

343
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,402
He'll come back,

344
00:23:20,010 --> 00:23:23,600
act like nothing happened,
like he always does.

345
00:23:25,190 --> 00:23:26,379
Isn't that a good thing?

346
00:23:29,382 --> 00:23:30,499
Yeah, exactly.

347
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:35,397
So I don't get why he's mad.

348
00:23:39,148 --> 00:23:40,148
How about this?

349
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:41,602
When he comes back,

350
00:23:41,770 --> 00:23:43,401
wear the shirt to make up with him.

351
00:23:44,447 --> 00:23:45,697
I'm not making up with him.

352
00:23:47,748 --> 00:23:49,180
What? Then what?

353
00:23:49,204 --> 00:23:50,330
Want me to punch him?

354
00:23:50,752 --> 00:23:51,752
Hm?

355
00:23:53,768 --> 00:23:54,768
Here.

356
00:23:55,171 --> 00:23:56,807
This is Kongdech.

357
00:23:57,580 --> 00:23:58,580
Punch him.

358
00:23:59,072 --> 00:24:00,072
Come on.

359
00:24:01,177 --> 00:24:02,530
Here. Punch him.

360
00:24:04,430 --> 00:24:05,977
Here.

361
00:24:06,148 --> 00:24:07,302
Barth.

362
00:24:07,970 --> 00:24:08,970
What?

363
00:24:09,114 --> 00:24:10,780
See? Now you're smiling.

364
00:24:11,420 --> 00:24:12,800
Punch him. Here.

365
00:24:12,835 --> 00:24:14,385
Why would you do this?

366
00:24:14,671 --> 00:24:15,700
Ask him if it hurts.

367
00:24:16,432 --> 00:24:17,503
Does it hurt?

368
00:24:18,219 --> 00:24:19,402
What are you doing?

369
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,000
See? You can smile.

370
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:22,780
You two, tomorrow

371
00:24:26,733 --> 00:24:28,410
help me organize the library.

372
00:24:31,188 --> 00:24:32,188
Yes, sir.

373
00:24:53,736 --> 00:24:54,798
Joe…

374
00:24:55,010 --> 00:24:56,300
is seriously cool, isn't he?

375
00:24:57,134 --> 00:24:58,134
Mm.

376
00:24:59,038 --> 00:25:00,296
When he was here,

377
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,330
he was good at school, music, sports.

378
00:25:02,357 --> 00:25:03,357
Everything.

379
00:25:04,028 --> 00:25:05,299
His nickname

380
00:25:05,590 --> 00:25:07,330
was “the hope of his class.”

381
00:25:08,084 --> 00:25:10,302
Girls waited outside the church
for him every week.

382
00:25:10,521 --> 00:25:11,521
Wow.

383
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:13,565
If I were him,

384
00:25:13,632 --> 00:25:15,370
I'd feel so much pressure.

385
00:25:17,270 --> 00:25:18,702
But his heart was so steady.

386
00:25:20,278 --> 00:25:21,278
Yeah.

387
00:25:21,423 --> 00:25:24,197
I saw his eyes
during the guidance session.

388
00:25:24,417 --> 00:25:26,054
He didn't seem unsure at all.

389
00:25:26,965 --> 00:25:28,600
Where should I put these books?

390
00:25:30,514 --> 00:25:31,514
All the way at the back.

391
00:25:31,725 --> 00:25:33,202
But wipe the dust off first.

392
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:34,700
Got it.

393
00:25:36,499 --> 00:25:37,499
You two,

394
00:25:37,788 --> 00:25:38,900
go help him.

395
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:53,198
What about you, Tanrak?

396
00:25:54,714 --> 00:25:55,930
Have you ever had doubts?

397
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,040
Well,

398
00:26:01,517 --> 00:26:05,299
I've always pictured myself that way.

399
00:26:06,171 --> 00:26:07,171
A priest's robe.

400
00:26:07,931 --> 00:26:08,798
The altar.

401
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:10,900
And me standing there preaching.

402
00:26:11,551 --> 00:26:13,402
That's the picture I see most often.

403
00:26:17,216 --> 00:26:20,560
Then your heart
is just as steady as Joe's.

404
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,782
I wouldn't say that.

405
00:26:27,180 --> 00:26:28,397
My heart

406
00:26:28,847 --> 00:26:30,604
isn't that steady.

407
00:26:31,177 --> 00:26:32,202
There are still…

408
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:35,099
things that…

409
00:26:35,671 --> 00:26:36,802
make me…

410
00:26:37,075 --> 00:26:38,097
waver.

411
00:26:42,817 --> 00:26:43,817
Yeah.

412
00:26:44,942 --> 00:26:45,942
So,

413
00:26:46,711 --> 00:26:48,198
how do you deal with it?

414
00:26:51,093 --> 00:26:52,600
I'm trying.

415
00:26:52,626 --> 00:26:53,896
It's not easy.

416
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:57,120
Yeah.

417
00:26:57,388 --> 00:26:58,388
I know.

418
00:26:58,940 --> 00:26:59,940
It's hard.

419
00:27:06,110 --> 00:27:07,110
But…

420
00:27:08,177 --> 00:27:11,099
when I really think about it,

421
00:27:11,869 --> 00:27:13,400
if one day I have to choose,

422
00:27:13,881 --> 00:27:16,702
I'd choose God over anything else.

423
00:27:26,631 --> 00:27:27,696
What about you?

424
00:27:28,214 --> 00:27:30,299
Have you ever had doubts?

425
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,320
Well,

426
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:41,302
I have doubts all the time.

427
00:27:43,339 --> 00:27:45,580
You know how long this path is.

428
00:27:46,241 --> 00:27:47,702
Who knows what the future holds?

429
00:27:49,230 --> 00:27:51,297
Even you still has doubts?

430
00:27:53,551 --> 00:27:54,551
I don't know.

431
00:27:55,465 --> 00:27:57,102
Let's just say, in my class,

432
00:27:57,531 --> 00:27:59,097
there are only two of us left.

433
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,804
My family

434
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:05,099
has high hopes for me too.

435
00:28:06,270 --> 00:28:07,397
It's…

436
00:28:08,906 --> 00:28:10,401
kind of a lot of pressure.

437
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,897
Being expected to be something.

438
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:20,699
For me, it's more fear.

439
00:28:23,466 --> 00:28:24,897
I'm not afraid of God

440
00:28:28,232 --> 00:28:29,700
but of the people around me.

441
00:28:31,983 --> 00:28:33,897
Afraid I'll disappoint them, hurt them.

442
00:28:35,395 --> 00:28:36,800
Afraid they'll think I gave up,

443
00:28:37,176 --> 00:28:38,690
that I didn't have what it takes.

444
00:28:54,788 --> 00:28:56,601
But hey, if that day ever comes,

445
00:28:56,903 --> 00:28:58,502
that's their problem, isn't it?

446
00:29:00,570 --> 00:29:01,600
Then,

447
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:04,300
what are you living for now?

448
00:29:06,552 --> 00:29:07,699
What am I living for?

449
00:29:12,564 --> 00:29:13,703
Because I know

450
00:29:16,910 --> 00:29:19,096
I'm not here to be anyone's hope.

451
00:31:22,970 --> 00:31:23,983
What is it?

452
00:31:28,588 --> 00:31:29,985
Done helping Phak?

453
00:31:33,257 --> 00:31:34,257
Yeah.

454
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:47,500
The church with no one around

455
00:31:49,242 --> 00:31:50,242
is pretty quiet, huh?

456
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:55,540
Yeah.

457
00:31:57,259 --> 00:31:59,985
So quiet you can hear everything.

458
00:32:05,611 --> 00:32:06,611
So…

459
00:32:11,072 --> 00:32:13,001
have you heard the voice
inside your head yet?

460
00:33:19,425 --> 00:33:20,604
Were you waiting for me?

461
00:33:23,586 --> 00:33:24,586
No.

462
00:33:29,722 --> 00:33:30,722
Hey, wait.

463
00:33:40,238 --> 00:33:42,097
When you said you were wavering…

464
00:33:44,496 --> 00:33:45,897
is that all it is?

465
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:53,330
Well…

466
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:56,810
how could I feel
anything more than that, Barth?

467
00:34:00,220 --> 00:34:01,802
Can't you just let it happen?

468
00:34:05,650 --> 00:34:07,400
Let it go even further?

469
00:34:27,500 --> 00:34:28,500
Barth.

470
00:34:30,811 --> 00:34:31,811
You know what?

471
00:34:34,920 --> 00:34:36,299
When I'm near you,

472
00:34:38,700 --> 00:34:40,296
I can't control myself.

473
00:34:45,488 --> 00:34:47,195
But are you happy?

474
00:34:52,731 --> 00:34:53,731
Yeah.

475
00:35:05,167 --> 00:35:06,167
Barth.

476
00:35:06,617 --> 00:35:07,617
Barth.

477
00:35:09,004 --> 00:35:10,004
Barth.

478
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:14,602
Why are you calling me so loud?

479
00:35:16,288 --> 00:35:17,398
I'm right here.

480
00:35:21,414 --> 00:35:22,502
I'm not going anywhere.

481
00:35:30,948 --> 00:35:31,948
Thank you.

482
00:36:24,634 --> 00:36:27,801
The school at night
really is as quiet as you said.

483
00:36:30,580 --> 00:36:31,600
I like it.

484
00:36:36,670 --> 00:36:38,499
Have you been here since you were a kid?

485
00:36:39,974 --> 00:36:40,699
Hm?

486
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:41,903
I've…

487
00:36:44,688 --> 00:36:47,497
been here since Grade 7.

488
00:36:50,137 --> 00:36:53,974
I know the sound of the bell
better than my own front door.

489
00:36:57,190 --> 00:36:58,997
Wow. Didn't you get lonely?

490
00:37:00,597 --> 00:37:03,574
I can't even imagine it.

491
00:37:06,470 --> 00:37:07,470
Lonely?

492
00:37:08,330 --> 00:37:09,497
I…

493
00:37:11,070 --> 00:37:12,601
Didn't understand it as a kid.

494
00:37:15,220 --> 00:37:16,900
Now that you're older, do you?

495
00:37:17,617 --> 00:37:19,697
I think I understand it more now.

496
00:37:20,303 --> 00:37:22,300
I don't feel lonely like I used to.

497
00:37:30,074 --> 00:37:31,074
What's wrong?

498
00:37:31,151 --> 00:37:33,097
There's something I want to tell you, but…

499
00:37:33,740 --> 00:37:34,675
Okay.

500
00:37:34,748 --> 00:37:36,198
I'll tell you.

501
00:37:37,348 --> 00:37:38,602
When I was little,

502
00:37:39,210 --> 00:37:44,602
I cried every day
when I first moved into the dorm.

503
00:37:45,610 --> 00:37:46,903
But I was embarrassed.

504
00:37:47,466 --> 00:37:50,300
So I had to cry alone
in the bathroom.

505
00:37:53,982 --> 00:37:54,982
Seriously?

506
00:37:55,450 --> 00:37:56,900
So you were a crybaby.

507
00:38:04,247 --> 00:38:05,503
Hey, wait.

508
00:38:06,638 --> 00:38:07,696
I have a question.

509
00:38:08,666 --> 00:38:12,800
What if you had a choice,

510
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:15,200
would you choose this path?

511
00:38:19,918 --> 00:38:20,918
No.

512
00:38:23,610 --> 00:38:24,610
You wouldn't?

513
00:38:26,690 --> 00:38:27,770
I'm not telling.

514
00:38:28,539 --> 00:38:29,539
Not telling?

515
00:38:31,820 --> 00:38:32,820
Tanrak.

516
00:38:33,430 --> 00:38:34,222
Tell me.

517
00:38:34,282 --> 00:38:35,111
No.

518
00:38:35,140 --> 00:38:37,176
- Come on. Tell me.
- No.

519
00:38:39,082 --> 00:38:40,697
Whisper it. No one will know.

520
00:38:41,930 --> 00:38:42,930
I'm not telling.

521
00:38:47,080 --> 00:38:48,080
Hey, Tan.

522
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,000
Come on.

523
00:38:52,557 --> 00:38:53,557
Want to go?

524
00:39:02,702 --> 00:39:04,503
Hey. Wait.

525
00:39:04,669 --> 00:39:05,669
What are you doing?

526
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:08,800
Keeping watch over you.

527
00:39:10,167 --> 00:39:12,204
I'll stay here until I get an answer.

528
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,002
You really don't give up, do you?

529
00:39:21,890 --> 00:39:24,103
I'm not usually this persistent, you know.

530
00:39:27,244 --> 00:39:28,244
Just answer me.

531
00:39:28,779 --> 00:39:29,979
I really want to know.

532
00:39:31,900 --> 00:39:36,404
I'm not answering
because I really don't have an answer.

533
00:39:45,161 --> 00:39:46,161
You know,

534
00:39:47,465 --> 00:39:50,382
I've slept in this bed since Grade 7

535
00:39:51,357 --> 00:39:52,779
I've never changed beds.

536
00:39:56,288 --> 00:39:57,288
Tanrak.

537
00:40:01,072 --> 00:40:02,376
Can I sleep next to you?

538
00:40:08,230 --> 00:40:09,497
What's with you today?

539
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,720
You really want to be close to me.

540
00:40:20,001 --> 00:40:21,001
I'm lonely.

541
00:40:25,253 --> 00:40:27,200
Without you here,

542
00:40:30,577 --> 00:40:31,900
I'd be dying of loneliness.

543
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:42,200
Hey.

544
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:45,198
Thank you.

545
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:16,770
HAPPY NEW YEAR

546
00:41:17,299 --> 00:41:18,502
Okay, everyone.

547
00:41:19,422 --> 00:41:20,998
Father Arnon isn't here today.

548
00:41:21,706 --> 00:41:24,200
So… you get a free day.

549
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:28,299
You spilled the water.

550
00:41:31,278 --> 00:41:31,949
Master.

551
00:41:31,977 --> 00:41:33,400
Can I go watch a movie, then?

552
00:41:34,358 --> 00:41:36,696
Sure. I'll rent one for you.

553
00:41:41,002 --> 00:41:42,899
Wait, I totally forgot.

554
00:41:43,594 --> 00:41:45,576
The church needs our help today.

555
00:41:45,750 --> 00:41:47,470
They're setting up
for the New Year's party.

556
00:41:48,213 --> 00:41:50,697
Any volunteers?

557
00:41:53,623 --> 00:41:54,623
I'll go.

558
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,398
Okay, we've got one: Barth.

559
00:41:58,020 --> 00:42:01,297
Anyone else? Come on.

560
00:42:04,465 --> 00:42:05,465
Bird?

561
00:42:06,945 --> 00:42:07,945
Sak?

562
00:42:09,201 --> 00:42:11,601
Wow. You were so loud
asking to watch a movie.

563
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:14,702
Come on, have some heart.

564
00:42:15,322 --> 00:42:16,779
You're letting him go alone?

565
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:19,096
No one else?

566
00:42:20,097 --> 00:42:22,097
Master, I'll go too.

567
00:42:24,776 --> 00:42:25,776
Okay.

568
00:42:26,430 --> 00:42:31,102
Barth and Tanrak,
after you finish eating, come with me.

569
00:42:47,414 --> 00:42:48,800
You can wash this part first.

570
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:52,500
We only used these a few days ago.

571
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,804
Where did all this dust come from?

572
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:57,097
Can you wash this part for me?

573
00:43:15,414 --> 00:43:16,785
Man, it's hot out here.

574
00:43:17,710 --> 00:43:20,162
Barth, aim at the chairs.
You're spraying me instead.

575
00:43:22,110 --> 00:43:23,291
I'm cleansing your sins.

576
00:43:24,154 --> 00:43:25,176
You like that, don't you?

577
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:27,334
Cleansing sins?

578
00:43:27,973 --> 00:43:29,198
Then let me cleanse yours.

579
00:43:29,945 --> 00:43:31,903
Someone like you needs half a day.

580
00:43:33,230 --> 00:43:33,964
Tanrak.

581
00:43:34,186 --> 00:43:35,805
Tanrak, don't.

582
00:43:36,124 --> 00:43:37,490
God doesn't listen to me anyway.

583
00:43:37,517 --> 00:43:38,604
Wait.

584
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:41,404
Is this Songkran?

585
00:43:46,690 --> 00:43:47,497
Turn off the water.

586
00:43:47,641 --> 00:43:48,702
So hardworking.

587
00:43:48,958 --> 00:43:50,377
Even working on your day off.

588
00:43:54,204 --> 00:43:56,700
Aren't you going anywhere?

589
00:43:58,524 --> 00:43:59,524
How can we?

590
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:02,280
It's New Year's
and we're stuck working at church.

591
00:44:02,466 --> 00:44:03,579
Poor you.

592
00:44:04,235 --> 00:44:05,402
Where do you want to go?

593
00:44:07,539 --> 00:44:09,402
Anywhere without piles of chairs.

594
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:19,080
Here.

595
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:23,960
Wait.

596
00:44:30,075 --> 00:44:31,174
Fill up the gas too.

597
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:37,140
Hey.

598
00:44:37,590 --> 00:44:38,650
Want my Walkman too?

599
00:44:41,853 --> 00:44:42,902
That'd be nice.

600
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:51,440
Thank you.

601
00:44:52,902 --> 00:44:53,902
Let's go.

602
00:45:00,070 --> 00:45:01,400
Barth, hurry.

603
00:45:12,260 --> 00:45:13,096
Babe.

604
00:45:13,155 --> 00:45:14,155
Hm?

605
00:45:15,280 --> 00:45:17,360
You just made your friends
break the rules, you know.

606
00:45:18,779 --> 00:45:20,602
You're in on it too.

607
00:45:22,642 --> 00:45:24,500
Should I really lend them my bike?

608
00:45:26,893 --> 00:45:28,103
Let it slide.

609
00:45:32,290 --> 00:45:33,570
A troublemaker

610
00:45:33,990 --> 00:45:37,099
and a scholarship kid making trouble
aren't the same thing, you know.

611
00:45:41,619 --> 00:45:42,703
Then…

612
00:45:43,610 --> 00:45:45,797
if you were a Magdalene scholarship kid,

613
00:45:46,322 --> 00:45:47,700
would you still date me?

614
00:45:53,237 --> 00:45:54,237
Of course.

615
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:56,840
I would.

616
00:46:04,087 --> 00:46:04,721
Barth.

617
00:46:04,874 --> 00:46:06,200
They're having fun, aren't they?

618
00:46:06,626 --> 00:46:07,626
Want to join them?

619
00:46:51,832 --> 00:46:53,014
Do you have Modern Dog?

620
00:46:53,093 --> 00:46:54,093
One cassette left.

621
00:47:05,848 --> 00:47:06,894
How much is it?

622
00:47:06,991 --> 00:47:07,991
90.

623
00:47:08,148 --> 00:47:09,148
90.

624
00:47:10,471 --> 00:47:11,471
Here you go.

625
00:47:11,897 --> 00:47:12,897
Keep the change.

626
00:47:25,170 --> 00:47:26,170
MODERN DOG

627
00:47:48,952 --> 00:47:52,783
♪ Before the sky could turn so bright ♪

628
00:47:54,081 --> 00:47:57,900
♪ Before the sunlight warmed the day ♪

629
00:47:58,220 --> 00:48:02,697
♪ Before the flowers bloomed in sight ♪

630
00:48:02,970 --> 00:48:06,828
♪ Before sweet dreams
could find their way ♪

631
00:48:07,148 --> 00:48:10,000
♪ My heart had had no one ♪

632
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:12,802
♪ Until your love entered ♪

633
00:48:12,891 --> 00:48:17,045
♪ Filling my eyes bright with colors ♪

634
00:48:17,348 --> 00:48:20,383
♪ My side had had no one ♪

635
00:48:20,539 --> 00:48:23,202
♪ Until your love showed me grace ♪

636
00:48:23,445 --> 00:48:28,200
♪ To give me strength I never had ♪

637
00:48:32,392 --> 00:48:35,982
♪ Before the stars filled up the sky ♪

638
00:48:37,481 --> 00:48:41,336
♪ Before this life could feel its worth ♪

639
00:48:41,650 --> 00:48:45,198
♪ Before my faith all ran dry ♪

640
00:48:46,413 --> 00:48:49,899
♪ Before my fire was all burnt ♪

641
00:48:50,231 --> 00:48:53,497
♪ My heart had had no one ♪

642
00:48:53,721 --> 00:48:56,197
♪ Until your love entered ♪

643
00:48:56,285 --> 00:49:00,185
♪ Filling my eyes bright with colors ♪

644
00:49:00,210 --> 00:49:00,988
Woo!

645
00:49:01,078 --> 00:49:03,580
♪ My side had had no one ♪

646
00:49:03,946 --> 00:49:06,601
♪ Until your love showed me grace ♪

647
00:49:06,860 --> 00:49:10,786
♪ To give me strength I never had ♪

648
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:19,000
♪ To carry on in this cruel world ♪

649
00:49:40,656 --> 00:49:42,303
You really like this song, huh?

650
00:49:43,230 --> 00:49:46,779
♪ My heart, my soul ♪

651
00:49:48,011 --> 00:49:50,254
♪ Are yours to own ♪

652
00:49:53,462 --> 00:49:56,638
♪ All my life, I promise you ♪

653
00:49:58,251 --> 00:50:02,297
♪ I'll keep on fighting for you ♪

654
00:50:15,465 --> 00:50:16,465
Here.

655
00:50:17,832 --> 00:50:19,185
It's okay. You eat it.

656
00:50:28,931 --> 00:50:30,802
Once I found out why he wrote this song,

657
00:50:32,440 --> 00:50:34,004
I liked it even more.

658
00:50:43,851 --> 00:50:44,900
It's cool, right?

659
00:50:45,351 --> 00:50:50,096
Putting “you'd left” in the blanks.

660
00:50:51,745 --> 00:50:53,201
You'd left

661
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:57,102
before the sky could turn so bright.

662
00:50:59,096 --> 00:51:00,497
You'd left

663
00:51:02,032 --> 00:51:04,201
before the sunlight warmed the day.

664
00:51:07,349 --> 00:51:08,702
You'd left

665
00:51:10,660 --> 00:51:12,503
before the flowers bloomed in sight.

666
00:51:18,282 --> 00:51:19,602
You'd left

667
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:23,700
before sweet dreams could find their way.

668
00:51:28,023 --> 00:51:29,290
I wonder

669
00:51:30,296 --> 00:51:31,997
how my parents are doing now.

670
00:51:46,583 --> 00:51:47,583
Don't do that.

671
00:51:49,051 --> 00:51:51,103
Your parents are at peace now.

672
00:51:57,106 --> 00:51:59,896
I just wonder,

673
00:52:00,640 --> 00:52:02,201
if my parents were still here,

674
00:52:02,817 --> 00:52:04,700
would I still be who I am today?

675
00:52:09,075 --> 00:52:10,302
I can't even imagine it.

676
00:52:14,642 --> 00:52:15,642
Hey,

677
00:52:16,282 --> 00:52:17,977
your life is good, isn't it?

678
00:52:19,810 --> 00:52:20,970
Don't get stuck in your head.

679
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:23,973
You don't have to comfort me.

680
00:52:27,859 --> 00:52:29,201
I mean it.

681
00:52:31,653 --> 00:52:33,499
You're way stronger than you think.

682
00:52:34,730 --> 00:52:37,000
Your parents would be really proud of you.

683
00:52:39,151 --> 00:52:40,151
Look at me.

684
00:52:41,710 --> 00:52:43,296
I punched a friend and got expelled.

685
00:52:50,136 --> 00:52:51,136
Hey.

686
00:52:53,681 --> 00:52:54,700
I got it.

687
00:52:55,900 --> 00:53:00,099
I want to be
a gold-medal hero like Somrak.

688
00:53:03,630 --> 00:53:05,499
"I'm not bragging."

689
00:53:11,205 --> 00:53:14,099
I don't like serious stuff.

690
00:53:15,597 --> 00:53:16,802
And I'm not good at school.

691
00:53:18,380 --> 00:53:19,899
But you're good with computers.

692
00:53:26,672 --> 00:53:28,096
Should I open a computer shop?

693
00:53:28,776 --> 00:53:30,201
I'd play games all day.

694
00:53:43,414 --> 00:53:44,702
I don't want to go back yet.

695
00:53:46,745 --> 00:53:47,980
Who said I was going back?

696
00:54:46,620 --> 00:54:47,620
Be careful.

697
00:55:07,090 --> 00:55:09,795
Hey, look at this.

698
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:18,600
I carved my name here once.

699
00:55:25,488 --> 00:55:27,690
I even spelled my own name wrong
back then.

700
00:55:28,075 --> 00:55:29,404
Did you come here a lot?

701
00:55:30,500 --> 00:55:31,801
I used to come with my mom.

702
00:55:35,075 --> 00:55:36,075
My dad too.

703
00:55:41,890 --> 00:55:44,197
I used to think my family was normal.

704
00:55:48,362 --> 00:55:50,595
I didn't even know it wasn't.

705
00:55:54,990 --> 00:55:56,379
I saw my mom…

706
00:55:59,010 --> 00:56:00,801
with bruises almost every week.

707
00:56:03,450 --> 00:56:05,402
I saw her crying every day.

708
00:56:08,740 --> 00:56:11,505
As a kid, I thought,
maybe it was just grown-up stuff.

709
00:56:12,545 --> 00:56:14,801
But when I grew up, I knew it wasn't.

710
00:56:22,340 --> 00:56:23,597
My home was messed up.

711
00:56:27,856 --> 00:56:30,302
I once asked my mom,

712
00:56:34,250 --> 00:56:36,490
“Why stay together
if you don't love each other anymore?”

713
00:56:41,430 --> 00:56:42,499
She didn't answer.

714
00:56:43,918 --> 00:56:45,097
Neither did my dad.

715
00:56:49,019 --> 00:56:50,502
So back then, I thought

716
00:56:51,497 --> 00:56:52,601
maybe they…

717
00:56:55,090 --> 00:56:56,497
stayed because of me.

718
00:56:58,630 --> 00:56:59,902
But that wasn't it at all.

719
00:57:02,780 --> 00:57:04,773
My mom stayed because she feared sin.

720
00:57:06,386 --> 00:57:07,546
She feared breaking her vows.

721
00:57:12,880 --> 00:57:15,300
Feared God wouldn't forgive her
if she left her husband.

722
00:57:19,758 --> 00:57:20,688
So they just kept going

723
00:57:20,710 --> 00:57:22,590
even though they didn't love
each other anymore.

724
00:57:28,690 --> 00:57:30,299
If that was all, I could take it.

725
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:35,982
But it wasn't just that.

726
00:57:41,020 --> 00:57:43,400
In the name of the Father,

727
00:57:43,591 --> 00:57:44,367
and of the Son,

728
00:57:44,474 --> 00:57:45,568
and of the Holy Spirit.

729
00:57:46,020 --> 00:57:47,302
Lord,

730
00:57:47,817 --> 00:57:48,817
please…

731
00:57:51,976 --> 00:57:53,202
We weren't done praying.

732
00:57:54,988 --> 00:57:57,000
Barth, apologize to your father.

733
00:58:01,078 --> 00:58:02,078
I'm sorry.

734
00:58:05,940 --> 00:58:08,374
In the name of the Father,

735
00:58:08,632 --> 00:58:09,400
and of the Son,

736
00:58:09,520 --> 00:58:10,702
and of the Holy Spirit.

737
00:58:11,345 --> 00:58:12,496
Lord,

738
00:58:13,997 --> 00:58:17,360
please bless us and the food
we are about to eat,

739
00:58:17,988 --> 00:58:21,000
so we may live to serve You and others.

740
00:58:22,180 --> 00:58:23,899
In the name of the Father,

741
00:58:23,960 --> 00:58:25,520
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit.

742
00:58:26,459 --> 00:58:27,200
Amen.

743
00:58:27,422 --> 00:58:28,422
Amen.

744
00:58:32,807 --> 00:58:35,976
<i>One day, my dad found out I was gay.</i>

745
00:58:36,310 --> 00:58:37,500
What the hell is this?

746
00:58:37,710 --> 00:58:38,750
What kind of book is this?

747
00:58:38,877 --> 00:58:40,096
This filthy book is yours?

748
00:58:40,662 --> 00:58:41,662
What are you doing?

749
00:58:41,915 --> 00:58:42,915
It can be cured.

750
00:58:43,047 --> 00:58:44,374
God will help you.

751
00:58:44,560 --> 00:58:45,702
I'm not sick, Dad.

752
00:58:45,986 --> 00:58:47,198
Not sick?

753
00:58:48,555 --> 00:58:49,831
How could you do this?

754
00:58:49,859 --> 00:58:51,198
Is this how I raised you?

755
00:58:51,226 --> 00:58:51,866
Don't!

756
00:58:51,896 --> 00:58:53,136
You make me ashamed before God.

757
00:58:54,561 --> 00:58:55,902
Please don't! Don't do this!

758
00:58:55,985 --> 00:58:57,041
Stay out of it!

759
00:58:58,142 --> 00:58:59,142
Mom, help me!

760
00:58:59,168 --> 00:59:00,897
You can't be like this.

761
00:59:01,438 --> 00:59:03,580
Is this who you've become?

762
00:59:04,075 --> 00:59:05,597
You make me ashamed before God.

763
00:59:06,623 --> 00:59:08,038
How could you do this?

764
00:59:17,502 --> 00:59:18,502
Mom! Mom!

765
00:59:18,918 --> 00:59:20,382
Mom, stop!

766
00:59:20,874 --> 00:59:21,874
Mom, that's enough.

767
00:59:36,471 --> 00:59:37,494
Barth.

768
00:59:38,660 --> 00:59:40,810
<i>I never thought it would get that bad.</i>

769
00:59:47,614 --> 00:59:48,703
My dad died.

770
00:59:50,057 --> 00:59:51,200
My mom went to prison.

771
00:59:51,644 --> 00:59:53,100
So I ended up as a scholarship kid.

772
00:59:56,420 --> 00:59:59,201
Are you still going to ask me
why I don't believe in God?

773
01:00:06,271 --> 01:00:07,503
I used to pray, you know.

774
01:00:10,299 --> 01:00:11,598
I prayed every day.

775
01:00:13,490 --> 01:00:16,721
I prayed for my dad
to stop hurting my mom.

776
01:00:16,752 --> 01:00:18,402
For my mom to stop crying.

777
01:00:18,632 --> 01:00:19,694
For things to get better.

778
01:00:19,730 --> 01:00:22,600
For my home to be normal again.
But it wasn't normal.

779
01:00:25,967 --> 01:00:27,500
I guess God was busy.

780
01:00:31,794 --> 01:00:34,402
Or maybe He thought
my family deserved all of it.

781
01:00:51,580 --> 01:00:53,980
I just don't know
how I'm supposed to believe in God.

782
01:01:01,214 --> 01:01:02,214
Then…

783
01:01:04,391 --> 01:01:06,503
I'll pray to God for your mom.

784
01:01:14,774 --> 01:01:15,774
Thanks.

785
01:01:23,002 --> 01:01:24,002
Hey.

786
01:01:28,700 --> 01:01:29,899
Come on, we're on a trip.

787
01:01:30,287 --> 01:01:31,598
Why the gloomy face?

788
01:01:39,371 --> 01:01:40,897
I want you to remember

789
01:01:41,714 --> 01:01:43,604
our first waterfall trip

790
01:01:44,826 --> 01:01:46,204
as something happier than this.

791
01:02:04,911 --> 01:02:07,060
Don't tell me this is your first time
at a waterfall.

792
01:02:10,260 --> 01:02:11,296
Can you believe it?

793
01:02:11,610 --> 01:02:13,102
I live in this province,

794
01:02:13,506 --> 01:02:16,000
but this is my first time at a waterfall.

795
01:02:35,980 --> 01:02:38,697
Too bad I didn't bring a camera.

796
01:02:39,875 --> 01:02:40,897
You don't need it.

797
01:02:41,770 --> 01:02:44,201
Next time you want to come, tell me.
I'll bring you here.

798
01:02:46,730 --> 01:02:47,899
I'm holding you to that.

799
01:02:49,573 --> 01:02:51,400
If I'm bluffing, may my house blow up.

800
01:02:53,691 --> 01:02:55,708
♪ With you right here ♪

801
01:02:55,734 --> 01:02:58,198
♪ With us right here ♪

802
01:02:58,503 --> 01:03:01,998
♪ There's nowhere else I'd rather be ♪

803
01:03:02,117 --> 01:03:04,200
♪ Every second ♪

804
01:03:04,305 --> 01:03:06,300
♪ That I have you near ♪

805
01:03:06,590 --> 01:03:10,600
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

806
01:03:11,110 --> 01:03:16,102
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

807
01:03:16,361 --> 01:03:19,592
♪ And hold this moment
for as long as I can ♪

808
01:03:19,752 --> 01:03:24,303
♪ If heaven is real,
how beautiful could it be ♪

809
01:03:24,462 --> 01:03:28,699
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

810
01:03:29,014 --> 01:03:33,765
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

811
01:03:33,800 --> 01:03:39,991
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

812
01:03:55,845 --> 01:03:58,768
♪ Every second ♪
♪ From that moment ♪

813
01:03:58,822 --> 01:04:00,585
♪ I have you near ♪
♪ I have you near ♪

814
01:04:00,635 --> 01:04:04,598
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

815
01:04:04,894 --> 01:04:09,997
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

816
01:04:10,245 --> 01:04:13,404
♪ And hold this moment
for as long as I can ♪

817
01:04:13,530 --> 01:04:15,845
♪ If heaven is real ♪
♪ If it's not real ♪

818
01:04:15,882 --> 01:04:17,979
♪ How beautiful could it be ♪

819
01:04:18,282 --> 01:04:22,500
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

820
01:04:22,816 --> 01:04:27,583
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

821
01:04:27,619 --> 01:04:34,303
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

822
01:04:39,680 --> 01:04:44,410
BATH TANRAK

823
01:04:53,340 --> 01:04:56,302
(Next Episode) You're going on to
the seminary with Kongdech, right?

824
01:04:57,798 --> 01:04:58,450
Right?

825
01:04:58,725 --> 01:05:00,197
I'm asking you seriously, Tanrak.

826
01:05:00,610 --> 01:05:02,090
That calling from God you hear…

827
01:05:02,620 --> 01:05:04,201
is it still as loud as it used to be?

828
01:05:04,662 --> 01:05:05,662
I love you so much.

829
01:05:06,080 --> 01:05:07,300
I love you so much, Barth.

830
01:05:07,626 --> 01:05:08,626
I'm tired.

831
01:05:08,862 --> 01:05:10,458
Tired of having to hide this relationship.

832
01:05:10,482 --> 01:05:12,610
I don't care how God says this is wrong.

833
01:05:12,765 --> 01:05:13,902
You can't not care.

834
01:05:14,211 --> 01:05:16,602
God always gives us chances, Tanrak.

835
01:05:17,697 --> 01:05:19,173
But His path…

836
01:05:20,097 --> 01:05:21,296
is not easy at all.

